Madison McCallum of Skate Brandon earned a second-place finish at the Sask Skate Invitational on the weekend in Regina. 
McCallum was second in junior ladies with a score of 98.70, while Tori Thiessen (86.31) was fourth and their teammate, Kirsten Gutenberg, (74.64) was seventh. Casey Bertholet of Skate Brandon was third in novice ladies at 83.19 points, while Julia Patenaude (57.71) and Anika Duguay (51.81) were 12th and 17th, respectively, in pre-novice ladies. In the Open event, Marijka Popadynetz (49.04) was seventh in the pre-novice ladies’ first flight. Erica Forsyth (40.28) was ninth in the third flight, while Taryn Gwynne (46.02) was in 11th the fourth flight. Please subscribe to view full article.
